How do we know our asthma is controlled? / goals of treatment
- Daytime symptoms <= 2
- NO nighttime
- Minimal use of reliever <= 2 times weekly
- No limitations to activity due to asthma

In other words: good asthma control means normal activity, normal sleep, minimal daytime symptoms, no hospital visits for asthma!

